children.text: There are areas where the L wall bracket has not been properly fixed to the trusses and top plates as specified by the manufacturer.
The truss manufacturer’s installation instructions state that there should be 3 nails into the roof member, and 4 nails into the wall top plate. It also states that
‘Internal Wall Bracket nailed to middle of slot. Leave gap between nail head and bracket to allow for vertical movement of truss on loading’ .
The fixing of these brackets must be rectified in accordance with the manufacturer’s requirements.
